Student Report App
Welcome to the Student Report App! This is a web application built using Flask to manage and view student reports. Users can add new students and view their reports easily.

Features
Add new students and their details.
View student reports in an organized format.
Deployed and accessible online through Heroku.

How to Access the App
You can access the live version of the app by clicking the link below:

[Student Report App](https://studentreportapp-3a01bda32f03.herokuapp.com/)

Deployment
The app is hosted on Heroku, providing an easy way to access it online. It uses a Flask web server and Gunicorn for production readiness.

Running the Application Locally
If you'd like to run the app on your own machine, follow these steps:

Clone the repository to your local machine.
Set up a virtual environment.
Install the necessary dependencies.
Run the app with a local server.

Tech Stack
Flask: A lightweight Python web framework.
Gunicorn: A WSGI server for production deployment of Flask apps.
Heroku: The platform used for deploying the app.

Contributing
If you want to contribute to this project, feel free to fork the repository, create a branch, and submit a pull request. Please ensure that you follow best practices and write clear commit messages.

